<p>I would like to get started with polymer and rails, so far I have managed to figure out that the official gems are <a href="https://github.com/alchapone/polymer-rails" rel="nofollow">polymer-rails</a> and <a href="https://github.com/alchapone/polymer-elements-rails" rel="nofollow">polymer-elements-rails</a></p>  <p>Here is my process:</p>  <p>add the gems to /Gemfile</p>  <pre><code>gem 'polymer-rails' gem 'polymer-elements-rails' </code></pre>  <p>run the bundler</p>  <pre><code>$ bundle </code></pre>  <p>install polymer</p>  <pre><code>$ rails g polymer:install </code></pre>  <p>which adds all the required dependancies.</p>  <p>in app/views/layouts/application.html.erb I add the following in the head tag:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%= html_import_tag 'application' %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>in app/assets/components/application.html.erb I added</p>  <pre><code>//= require polymer/polymer //= require paper-button/paper-button </code></pre>  <p>now in my index.html.erb</p>  <pre><code>&lt;paper-button&gt;Flat button&lt;/paper-button&gt; </code></pre>  <p>when I run the site it seems to work, however there is no styling.  When I inspect the element in the DOM, this is what I get:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;paper-button role="button" tabindex="0" aria-disabled="false" class="x-scope paper-button-0"&gt;Flat button&lt;/paper-button&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However there is no styling on the button, this is what i get: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/sq644.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/sq644.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>What am I doing wrong? Also has anyone tried using HAML with polymer?</p>